FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1782294489
OL,3,CSchools announce early closures to
OL,4,Cprotect pupils in extreme heat
OL,6,FThe red alert indicates "a risk to
OL,7,Flife for even the healthy population"
OL,8,Fas well as impacts beyond health and
OL,9,Fsocial care, with potential effects on
OL,10,Ftransport systems, food, water, energy
OL,11,Fsupplies and businesses.
OL,13,FIt is the second red heat health
OL,14,Fwarning to be issued, after the first
OL,15,Fin July 2022 when temperatures soared
OL,16,Fabove 40C in the UK for the first time.
OL,18,FSchool leaders' union NAHT has sent
OL,19,Fits members guidance on dealing with
OL,20,Fthe heat.
OL,26,@nD@YOUoD@eO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1782294489
OL,3,CSchools announce early closures to
OL,4,Cprotect pupils in extreme heat
OL,6,FGeneral secretary Paul Whiteman said:
OL,7,F"As temperatures continue to rise,
OL,8,Fschool leaders will be thinking
OL,9,Fcarefully about how to keep pupils and
OL,10,Fstaff safe and as comfortable as
OL,11,Fpossible.
OL,13,F"While there is no legal 'upper limit'
OL,14,Ffor temperature in schools, they will
OL,15,Fcertainly be doing all they can to
OL,16,Fmitigate the effects of such high
OL,17,Ftemperatures.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1782294489
OL,3,CSchools announce early closures to
OL,4,Cprotect pupils in extreme heat
OL,6,F"For most, this will mean making
OL,7,Fstraightforward adjustments such as
OL,8,Flimiting the time spent in the sun
OL,9,Fduring breaks, ensuring additional
OL,10,Fwater is available, making adjustments
OL,11,Fto uniform expectations where
OL,12,Fappropriate, and ventilating
OL,13,Fclassrooms as best they can.
OL,15,F"If, as it appears, warmer summers are
OL,16,Fgoing to become the norm, then
OL,17,FGovernment really does need to act
OL,18,Fmore urgently to improve and modernise
OL,19,Fschool buildings, including a focus on
OL,20,Fventilation and potentially air
OL,21,Fconditioning.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1782294489
OL,3,CSchools announce early closures to
OL,4,Cprotect pupils in extreme heat
OL,6,F"School buildings need to be conducive
OL,7,Fto learning all year round."
OL,9,FThe Department for Education said it
OL,10,Fdoes not normally advise schools to
OL,11,Fclose during hot weather because
OL,12,Fattendance is "the best way for pupils
OL,13,Fto learn and reach their potential",
OL,14,Fbut that school leaders should ensure
OL,15,Fthey take "any steps necessary to make
OL,16,Fsure children are safe and
OL,17,Fcomfortable", as it laid out guidance
OL,18,Fon how to keep pupils safe.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@\O]tD@OOUuD@cO]wD@KOUyD@LO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
