OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1782294489
OL,3,CSchools announce early closures to
OL,4,Cprotect pupils in extreme heat
OL,6,FFire chiefs are urging the public to
OL,7,Ftake extra care in outdoor spaces as
OL,8,Fthis week's "dangerous" heatwave
OL,9,Fincreases the risk of wildfires and
OL,10,Fwater-related deaths as people flock
OL,11,Foutdoors to enjoy the sunshine.
OL,13,FPhil Garrigan, National Fire Chiefs
OL,14,FCouncil (NFCC) chairman, said: "We
OL,15,Fhave already seen the consequences
OL,16,Fthat periods of extreme heat can have,
OL,17,Fwith a number of lives tragically lost
OL,18,Fin water-related incidents during
OL,19,Frecent hot weather.
OL,26,@pD@MOUpD@WO]vD@`OU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
